        "kind": "pull_request",
        "title": "fix(whatsapp): Add group admin privacy controls",
        "body": "Closes #69233\n\n## What changed\n\nThis adds an optional per-group WhatsApp admin override via `channels.whatsapp.groups.<jid>.admin` and wildcard `channels.whatsapp.groups.\"*\".admin`.\n\nWhen an admin is configured for a group scope:\n- the configured E.164 number bypasses mention gating for that group\n- non-admin group members cannot run slash commands in that group\n- the configured admin remains able to run slash commands for that group\n\nWhen no admin is configured, the existing group command authorization behavior is preserved.\n\n## Why\n\nThe issue described a privacy gap in mixed-trust WhatsApp groups: non-admin members could still probe bot behavior through mentions and slash commands. The first pass of this feature covered the basic config and enforcement, but upstream readiness also needed the behavior pinned down for wildcard group config and for the no-admin-configured fallback path.\n\n## User impact\n\nUsers can now designate a WhatsApp group admin by phone number and use that as a privacy boundary for command discovery in group chats.\n\nThis is intentionally backwards-compatible:\n- groups without `admin` continue using the existing command authorization rules\n- exact-group and wildcard group config both work\n- docs now describe the new config key\n\n## Root cause\n\nOpenClaw already had group policy, allowlists, and mention gating, but it did not have a per-group owner/admin concept for WhatsApp. That meant there was no narrow way to let a trusted operator manage the bot in a group without exposing command access to other participants covered by broader allowlist rules.\n\n## Validation\n\n- `npm exec pnpm@10.9.0 -- test extensions/whatsapp/src/group-policy.test.ts`\n- `npm exec pnpm@10.9.0 -- test extensions/whatsapp/src/inbound/access-control.test.ts`\n- `npm exec pnpm@10.9.0 -- test extensions/whatsapp/src/auto-reply/monitor/group-activation.test.ts`\n- `npm exec pnpm@10.9.0 -- test src/config/config.schema-regressions.test.ts`\n- `npm exec pnpm@10.9.0 -- test extensions/whatsapp/src`\n- `npm exec pnpm@10.9.0 -- tsgo:core`\n- `npm exec pnpm@10.9.0 -- tsgo:extensions`\n- `npm exec pnpm@10.9.0 -- check`\n- `npm exec pnpm@10.9.0 -- build`\n\n## AI assistance\n\n- AI-assisted: yes, with Codex\n- Testing: fully tested locally with the commands listed above\n- Bot review threads addressed and resolved after follow-up fixes",
